  "remarks" : " The binary relationship form of the congruence predicate.  The statement ` <. A , B >. Cgr <. C , D >. ` should be read informally as \"the ` N ` dimensional point ` A ` is as far from ` B ` as ` C ` is from ` D ` , or \"the line segment ` A B ` is congruent to the line segment ` C D ` . This particular definition is encapsulated by Tarski's axioms later on. (Contributed by Scott Fenton, 3-Jun-2013.) ",
  "statement" : "brcgr $p |- ( ( ( A e. ( EE ` N ) /\\ B e. ( EE ` N ) ) /\\ ( C e. ( EE ` N ) /\\ D e. ( EE ` N ) ) ) -> ( <. A , B >. Cgr <. C , D >. <-> sum_ i e. ( 1 ... N ) ( ( ( A ` i ) - ( B ` i ) ) ^ 2 ) = sum_ i e. ( 1 ... N ) ( ( ( C ` i ) - ( D ` i ) ) ^ 2 ) ) ) $.\n$d A i $.\n$d B i $.\n$d C i $.\n$d D i $.\n$d N i $."
